-- BBC May Announce New Director General Today, Guardian Says
-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n   a n d   M a r i a   T a d e o
-- 2012-07-04T07:41:59Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-04/bbc-may-announce-new-director-general-today-guardian-says.html
The British Broadcasting Corp.’s next
director general may be announced today, according to the
 Guardian  newspaper. The shortlisted candidates include the
broadcaster’s current chief operating officer, Caroline Thomson,
 BBC  Vision director George Entwistle, and the chief executive
officer of the country’s broadcasting regulator, Ed Richards,
the newspaper reported, without revealing where the information
came from.  A fourth candidate could enter the race for the BBC’s top
job but their identity is not known, according to the Guardian.  To contact the reporters on this story:
